-- Fiat's Iveco Chief to Leave as Part of Broad Restructuting, Corriere Says
-- Armorel Kenna
-- 2010-07-30T06:15:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/fiat-s-iveco-chief-to-leave-as-part-of-broad-restructuting-corriere-says.html

          
          
             Fiat SpA’s truck unit Iveco SpA will
be restructured over the next few months and managers, including
Chief Executive Officer Paolo Monferino will leave their posts,
daily Corriere della Sera reported, without saying where it got
the information.  
 Other managers, including Fiat Automobiles Chief Executive
Officer Lorenzo Sistino, may be moved to new posts, as part of
the unit’s spinoff in announced for 2011, the Italian newspaper
reported.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Armorel Kenna in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        